  description: "concurrent.futures.wait.__doc__.__len__() == 1054 — concurrent.futures.wait.__doc__ is a 1054-char multi-section doc (Args, Returns, Raises) describing the wait() function that blocks until futures complete or timeout expires; wait.__qualname__=='wait' (len=4); wait.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24); wait co_argcount==3; NEW in extra140: first standalone wait doc length invariant; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
